House Speaker John Boehner teared up on Tuesday as he led a ceremony to award a special band of World War II solders the Congressional Gold Medal. 

About 200 people attended the award ceremony to honor the 1st Special Force - also known as the Devil's Brigade - including about 40 remaining members of the elite group of American and Canadian soldiers.

'These men saved the free world,' Rep Boehner, R-Ohio, said at the Tuesday event where he was pictured wiping away tears from his face. 

